If a Java bean method name contains a number followed by a letter, such as hel2lo,  the axis runtime will upper case the letter L after the number 2.  This causes the exception below to occur.  

To reproduce this problem use the following java bean to go through a bottom up scenario.

package test;

public class Echo {
  public String hel2lo( String value )
  {
	  return value;
  }
}

This problem is probably in the Axis emitter.  Hopefully, there is a parameter on the Axis emitter call that can be used to turn off the name munging.  If there isn't parameter for this then an Axis bug should be opend to not change the case of method names.

